I do not think it is worthwhile having byte arrays as keys for efficiency's sake. I think it would be worthwhile from a *usability/understandability* point of view. If we had byte string keys it would be super clear how to sort the keys on both client and server, there is no opportunity for using the wrong locale or sorting function, and there's no "missing feature" of having locale-aware key sorting (because nobody expects that of byte arrays).

